		</header>

		
		<div class="g1-content-narrow g1-typography-xl entry-content" itemprop="articleBody" >
			<!-- WP QUADS Content Ad Plugin v. 2.0.8.3 -->
<div class="quads-location quads-ad1" id="quads-ad1" style="float:none;margin:0px 0 0px 0;text-align:center;">
<script async src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
<!-- 336x280, created 11/12/10 Hot Job Searches -->
<ins class="adsbygoogle"
     style="display:inline-block;width:336px;height:280px"
     data-ad-client="ca-pub-6069192697377457"
     data-ad-slot="7886540630"></ins>
<script>
(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script>
</div>
<p class="story-body__introduction">US<a href="https://howafrica.com/"> </a>President<a href="https://howafrica.com/"> </a>Donald Trump and North Korean leader Kim Jong-un have arrived in Singapore for their historic summit.</p>
<p>Mr Trump flew in aboard Air Force One, a few hours after Mr Kim touched down with his entourage.</p>
<p>The two men are staying in separate hotels, not far from each other, and are preparing for Tuesday&#8217;s meeting on the resort island of Sentosa.</p>
<p>Mr Kim told Singapore&#8217;s PM &#8220;the entire world is watching&#8221;. Mr Trump has called it a &#8220;one-time shot&#8221; at peace.</p>
<p>The US hopes the summit will kick-start a process that eventually sees Mr Kim give up nuclear weapons.</p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-126374 jetpack-lazy-image" src="https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt1.jpg?resize=592%2C398&#038;ssl=1" alt width="592" height="398" data-recalc-dims="1" data-lazy-srcset="https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt1.jpg?w=592&amp;ssl=1 592w, https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt1.jpg?resize=364%2C245&amp;ssl=1 364w, https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt1.jpg?resize=313%2C210&amp;ssl=1 313w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 592px) 100vw, 592px" data-lazy-src="https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt1.jpg?resize=592%2C398&amp;is-pending-load=1#038;ssl=1" srcset="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7"><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-126374" src="https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt1.jpg?resize=592%2C398&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="592" height="398" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt1.jpg?w=592&amp;ssl=1 592w, https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt1.jpg?resize=364%2C245&amp;ssl=1 364w, https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt1.jpg?resize=313%2C210&amp;ssl=1 313w" sizes="(max-width: 592px) 100vw, 592px" data-recalc-dims="1" /></noscript> <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-126375 jetpack-lazy-image" src="https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt3.jpg?resize=595%2C392&#038;ssl=1" alt width="595" height="392" data-recalc-dims="1" data-lazy-srcset="https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt3.jpg?w=595&amp;ssl=1 595w, https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt3.jpg?resize=364%2C240&amp;ssl=1 364w, https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt3.jpg?resize=313%2C206&amp;ssl=1 313w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 595px) 100vw, 595px" data-lazy-src="https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt3.jpg?resize=595%2C392&amp;is-pending-load=1#038;ssl=1" srcset="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7"><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-126375" src="https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt3.jpg?resize=595%2C392&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="595" height="392" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt3.jpg?w=595&amp;ssl=1 595w, https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt3.jpg?resize=364%2C240&amp;ssl=1 364w, https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt3.jpg?resize=313%2C206&amp;ssl=1 313w" sizes="(max-width: 595px) 100vw, 595px" data-recalc-dims="1" /></noscript></p>
<p>The two leaders have had an extraordinary up-and-down relationship over the past 18 months, trading insults and threatening war before abruptly changing tack and moving towards a face-to-face meeting.</p>
<h2 class="story-body__crosshead">How has the day unfolded?</h2>
<p>Because so little is known about the reclusive North Korean leader, even the plane he would be flying in from Pyongyang to Singapore became the subject of speculation.</p>
<p>The BBC&#8217;s Rupert Wingfield-Hayes said three aircraft took off from Pyongyang &#8211; an Ilyushin transport plane carrying Mr Kim&#8217;s armoured limousine, then an Air China 747 which normally carries the Chinese<a href="https://howafrica.com/category/african-celeb-profiles/"> president</a>, and lastly Mr Kim&#8217;s personal jet, a Soviet-era Ilyushin 62.</p>
<p>It eventually became apparent that he had arrived in the Air China plane after Singapore&#8217;s foreign minister posted a photo of him greeting Mr Kim on Instagram.</p>
<p>Secrecy surrounded the five-star St Regis hotel where he is staying too. Only North Korean media workers, dressed in identical black suits, were able to move freely around the building and tourists taking photos in communal areas were accosted by guards, Reuters news agency reported.</p>
<p>Mr Trump landed in Singapore later in the evening having flown from a contentious G7 meeting in Canada. He told a reporter he felt &#8220;very good&#8221; about the summit before heading to his hotel, the Shangri La, about half a mile from Mr Kim&#8217;s.</p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-126376 jetpack-lazy-image" src="https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt4.jpg?resize=590%2C383&#038;ssl=1" alt width="590" height="383" data-recalc-dims="1" data-lazy-srcset="https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt4.jpg?w=590&amp;ssl=1 590w, https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt4.jpg?resize=364%2C236&amp;ssl=1 364w, https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt4.jpg?resize=313%2C203&amp;ssl=1 313w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px" data-lazy-src="https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt4.jpg?resize=590%2C383&amp;is-pending-load=1#038;ssl=1" srcset="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7"><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-126376" src="https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt4.jpg?resize=590%2C383&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="590" height="383" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt4.jpg?w=590&amp;ssl=1 590w, https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt4.jpg?resize=364%2C236&amp;ssl=1 364w, https://i0.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt4.jpg?resize=313%2C203&amp;ssl=1 313w" sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px" data-recalc-dims="1" /></noscript></p>
<h2 class="story-body__crosshead">How did we get here?</h2>
<p>Mr Trump&#8217;s first year in office was marked by bitter exchanges with Mr Kim as North Korea conducted several ballistic missile tests in defiance of international warnings.</p>
<p>The US<a href="https://howafrica.com/category/african-celeb-profiles/"> president</a> vowed to unleash &#8220;fire and fury&#8221; if Pyongyang kept threatening the US. He also referred to Mr Kim as &#8220;little rocket man&#8221;.</p>
<p>In return, Mr Kim called him &#8220;mentally deranged&#8221; and a &#8220;dotard&#8221;.</p>
<p>Despite the White House&#8217;s &#8220;maximum pressure&#8221; campaign, the North remained defiant and carried out its sixth nuclear test in September 2017. Soon after, Mr Kim declared that his country had achieved its mission of becoming a nuclear state, with missiles that could reach the US.</p>
<!-- WP QUADS Content Ad Plugin v. 2.0.8.3 -->
