<figure class="media-with-caption">
<div class="player-with-placeholder"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-126372 jetpack-lazy-image" src="https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt.jpg?resize=600%2C409&#038;ssl=1" alt width="600" height="409" data-recalc-dims="1" data-lazy-srcset="https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt.jpg?resize=364%2C248&amp;ssl=1 364w, https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt.jpg?resize=313%2C213&amp;ssl=1 313w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-lazy-src="https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt.jpg?resize=600%2C409&amp;is-pending-load=1#038;ssl=1" srcset="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7"><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-126372" src="https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt.jpg?resize=600%2C409&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="600" height="409" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt.jpg?resize=364%2C248&amp;ssl=1 364w, https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt.jpg?resize=313%2C213&amp;ssl=1 313w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" /></noscript> <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-126373 jetpack-lazy-image" src="https://i2.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt2.jpg?resize=594%2C396&#038;ssl=1" alt width="594" height="396" data-recalc-dims="1" data-lazy-srcset="https://i2.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt2.jpg?w=594&amp;ssl=1 594w, https://i2.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt2.jpg?resize=364%2C243&amp;ssl=1 364w, https://i2.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt2.jpg?resize=313%2C209&amp;ssl=1 313w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 594px) 100vw, 594px" data-lazy-src="https://i2.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt2.jpg?resize=594%2C396&amp;is-pending-load=1#038;ssl=1" srcset="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7"><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-126373" src="https://i2.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt2.jpg?resize=594%2C396&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="594" height="396" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt2.jpg?w=594&amp;ssl=1 594w, https://i2.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt2.jpg?resize=364%2C243&amp;ssl=1 364w, https://i2.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tt2.jpg?resize=313%2C209&amp;ssl=1 313w" sizes="(max-width: 594px) 100vw, 594px" data-recalc-dims="1" /></noscript></div>
</figure>
<div class="sticky-player__player">
<p>But in early 2018, North Korea began attempts to improve relations with South Korea by sending a team and delegates to the Winter Olympics in Pyeongchang.</p>
<p>In March, Mr Trump surprised the world by accepting an invitation from Mr Kim &#8211; delivered via Seoul &#8211; to meet in person.</p>
<p>Since then, the path to the summit has been rocky, with Mr Trump at one point calling it off completely. But after some diplomatic scrambling, the two leaders will now sit down together.</p>
<p>Singapore is only the third country Mr Kim has visited since he became leader in 2011.</p>
<h2 class="story-body__crosshead">What do the two sides want?</h2>
<p>The US wants North Korea to get rid of its nuclear weapons in an irreversible manner that can be verified internationally. Only when steps begin to be taken in that direction will it &#8220;receive relief&#8221; from the grip of UN sanctions, Defence Secretary Jim Mattis recently said.</p>
<p>But this does not mean the US is expecting to get a final deal in Singapore. President Trump has described it as a &#8220;get-to-know-you situation&#8221; and said: &#8220;It&#8217;s going to be a process.&#8221;</p>
<ul class="story-body__unordered-list">
<li class="story-body__list-item">Who&#8217;s pulling the strings?</li>
<li class="story-body__list-item">Defectors: Stop romanticising a dictator</li>
<li class="story-body__list-item">Human rights not on the table</li>
</ul>
<p>Analysts say that Mr Kim, by winning the prestige of a meeting with the world&#8217;s most powerful leader, has already gained a victory. They also question why he would give up his nuclear weapons after pushing so hard to get them.</p>
<p>Some say he would never do it, unless everyone else on the Korean peninsula disarmed too &#8211; including the US.</p>
<figure><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-126370 jetpack-lazy-image" src="https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/101957540_047348419-1.jpg?resize=624%2C351&#038;ssl=1" alt width="624" height="351" data-recalc-dims="1" data-lazy-srcset="https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/101957540_047348419-1.jpg?w=624&amp;ssl=1 624w, https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/101957540_047348419-1.jpg?resize=192%2C108&amp;ssl=1 192w, https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/101957540_047348419-1.jpg?resize=384%2C216&amp;ssl=1 384w, https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/101957540_047348419-1.jpg?resize=364%2C205&amp;ssl=1 364w, https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/101957540_047348419-1.jpg?resize=561%2C316&amp;ssl=1 561w, https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/101957540_047348419-1.jpg?resize=608%2C342&amp;ssl=1 608w, https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/101957540_047348419-1.jpg?resize=313%2C176&amp;ssl=1 313w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 624px) 100vw, 624px" data-lazy-src="https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/101957540_047348419-1.jpg?resize=624%2C351&amp;is-pending-load=1#038;ssl=1" srcset="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7"><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-126370" src="https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/101957540_047348419-1.jpg?resize=624%2C351&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="624" height="351" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/101957540_047348419-1.jpg?w=624&amp;ssl=1 624w, https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/101957540_047348419-1.jpg?resize=192%2C108&amp;ssl=1 192w, https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/101957540_047348419-1.jpg?resize=384%2C216&amp;ssl=1 384w, https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/101957540_047348419-1.jpg?resize=364%2C205&amp;ssl=1 364w, https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/101957540_047348419-1.jpg?resize=561%2C316&amp;ssl=1 561w, https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/101957540_047348419-1.jpg?resize=608%2C342&amp;ssl=1 608w, https://i1.wp.com/howafrica.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/101957540_047348419-1.jpg?resize=313%2C176&amp;ssl=1 313w" sizes="(max-width: 624px) 100vw, 624px" data-recalc-dims="1" /></noscript></figure>
<figure class="media-landscape has-caption full-width"><span class="image-and-copyright-container"><span class="off-screen">Image copyright</span><span class="story-image-copyright">REUTERS</span></span><figcaption class="media-caption"><span class="off-screen">Image caption</span><span class="media-caption__text">The fine details of the summit have been worked out, even down to the recyclable cups</span></figcaption></figure>
<p>However, Mr Kim has also said he now wants to focus on building the North Korean economy &#8211; and thus wants sanctions relief and international investment.</p>
<p>The question is what concessions he is willing to make, and whether he will stick to any promises. Pledges to scrap the nuclear programme have been made before by his predecessors.</p>
<h2 class="story-body__crosshead">What could actually happen?</h2>
<p>It&#8217;s hard to say, but Mr Trump has signalled that they could sign an agreement to formally end the Korean War, which ended in a truce in 1953. Doing that would probably be &#8220;the easy part&#8221;, he said.</p>
<p>The US<a href="https://howafrica.com/category/politics/"> president</a> has also said that if he thinks things are going badly, he will walk out of the meeting, but if things go well, Mr Kim could receive an invitation to the White House.</p>
</div>

